I’m still in shock.  I have no words at the moment. I’m Grateful. 🙏🏾 I have a lot to smile about 😅🏆
16 years. For this ONE moment. And it was all worth it.  World champion. All praise to The Most High

I looked at my phone today and it showed me all my memories from October 11,2020. “On this day” I became a champion. 🏆 That season was a time of sacrifice & reinvention  for me and I will never forget that feeling of triumph. Leading up into that season I was traded and then waived. But that’s wasn’t the end! I wrote down all my goals and one of those goals was to become a champion. I transformed my mind, I transformed my body, and became closer to God. Next thing you know the Lakers called and that year we won a championship.I manifested it! The same way I manifested being the #1 player in high school, the same way I manifested being the #1 pick in the draft! I envisioned the end goal and then worked towards it until I got there.  That’s the lesson ! If you want something believe that you can get it, go out and do the work, and surely you will see it ! Faith + Works 🙏🏾 #nba #basketball #legend
Ran into @imdavisssyt after years since he attended my basketball camp 🙌🏾 He got a growth spurt 😂💪🏾 #hoop #dreams

La thank you. It was truly a pleasure being back in la. And winning a championship. I am very grateful to the Buss family, the Rambis family, the Pelinka’s and the entire laker organization. Lakernation. I love you💯💯Thank you for your support all year. This season was filled with emotion  and you guys stood strong with us all year. To my bro’s. We overcame a lot and won together. Thank you for the great memories we shared this season. I am forever grateful. We will always be champs. Nobody can take that away from us.🏆
